# Simulator Preview via serve-sim

After making code changes, build and preview in the iOS Simulator so you can visually verify the result.

## Simulator Details

- **Device:** iPhone 17 Pro (iOS 26.4)
- **UDID:** `A2EB7DAA-E049-4514-BCB6-C01ADD012BEC`
- **Bundle ID:** `SimeonRubin.ChoresApp`
- **Preview URL:** `http://localhost:3200`

## Step 1 — Ensure simulator is booted

```bash
xcrun simctl boot A2EB7DAA-E049-4514-BCB6-C01ADD012BEC 2>/dev/null || true
```

## Step 2 — Ensure serve-sim is running

```bash
npx serve-sim --list 2>/dev/null | grep -q "A2EB7DAA" || npx serve-sim --detach
# Then start the preview server if not running:
curl -sf http://localhost:3200 > /dev/null || (npx serve-sim &)
```

## Step 3 — Build for simulator

```bash
xcodebuild \
  -project ChoresApp.xcodeproj \
  -scheme ChoresApp \
  -destination 'id=A2EB7DAA-E049-4514-BCB6-C01ADD012BEC' \
  -configuration Debug \
  build \
  CODE_SIGNING_ALLOWED=YES \
  2>&1 | tail -20
```

## Step 4 — Install and launch on simulator

```bash
xcrun simctl install A2EB7DAA-E049-4514-BCB6-C01ADD012BEC \
  /Users/simeonrubin/Library/Developer/Xcode/DerivedData/ChoresApp-cxffvpxauigyvzaqawqntuvowfkm/Build/Products/Debug-iphonesimulator/ChoresApp.app

xcrun simctl launch --terminate-running-process A2EB7DAA-E049-4514-BCB6-C01ADD012BEC SimeonRubin.ChoresApp
```

## Step 5 — Visual verification

After launching, use the `cursor-ide-browser` MCP to navigate to `http://localhost:3200` and take a screenshot to visually confirm the UI looks correct. Report what you see.

## Rules

- Always run these steps after every set of code changes, before finishing your turn.
- If the build fails, fix errors and rebuild until it succeeds.
- Use the browser MCP to visually verify every significant UI change.
- Report the visual result (screenshot description) to the user.
